MCP Filesystem Setup Problem - Claude Desktop
Goal
Get MCP filesystem working in Claude Desktop to access AIKI_v3 project with 21,108 files and 996 folders.
System Info
* **OS**: Windows (MINGW64 terminal)
* **Claude**: Claude Desktop (latest)
* **Project location**: `C:\Users\jebal\AIKI_v3\`
* **Target files**: `memory_index.json`, `.copilot-instructions.md`, `MEMORY_IMPORT_INSTRUCTIONS.md`
What Works
1. âœ… **NPM installation successful**: `npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem` (added 128 packages)
2. âœ… **Manual server starts**: `npx @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem "C:\Users\jebal\AIKI_v3"` shows "Secure MCP Filesystem Server running on stdio"
3. âœ… **File paths verified**: Files definitely exist at specified locations
What Doesn't Work
âŒ **Claude Desktop can't read files**: All `window.fs.readFile()` calls return "File not found" even for:
