2. âœ… Added `-y` flag to npx command
3. âœ… Multiple Claude Desktop restarts
4. âœ… Verified config file location and syntax
5. âœ… Tested manual server startup (works)
6. âœ… Tried different path formats (forward/back slashes)
7. âœ… Tested relative paths
Technical Details
* `window.fs` object exists but `readFile()` fails on all files
* Error is always "File not found: No file named [path]"
* `window.fs.readdir()` gives "not a function" error
* Manual MCP server works but Claude Desktop can't connect to it
Key Question
**How to make Claude Desktop properly connect to and use the MCP filesystem server that we know is working?**
Files to Test With (confirmed to exist)
* `C:\Users\jebal\AIKI_v3\.copilot-instructions.md`
* `C:\Users\jebal\AIKI_v3\AIKI_CORE\consciousness\memory_index.json`
